本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:王俞翎研究生(外文):Wang,Yu-Ling論文名稱:台灣文化創意產業國際化之研究-以玻璃工藝為例論文名稱(外文):A Study of Internationalization on Culture Creative Industry in  Taiwan- Case of Glass Craft指導教授:吳銘達指導教授(外文):Wu, Ming-Ta學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立宜蘭大學系所名稱:經營管理研究所碩士班學門:商業及管理學門學類:企業管理學類論文出版年:2009畢業學年度:97語文別:中文論文頁數:169中文關鍵詞:文化創意產業、國際化、玻璃工藝外文關鍵詞:Culture Creative Industry、Internationalization、Glass Craft相關次數:

被引用:12點閱:2900評分:下載:1510書目收藏:6



在邁入知識經濟時代下，各國產業發展模式，正逐漸由工業化擴展至文化創意產業。目前歐美各國都將文化創意產業，視為國家發展經濟的重點策略，希望憑藉文化、創意、智力、科技，形成一個文化產業集群，提升其國際競爭力。台灣的產業發展除了面對其他三小龍: 南韓、新加坡、和香港的激烈競爭外，90年代起，又遭遇中國經濟崛起之另一競爭，迫使台灣產業發展，亦擴展至文化創意產業。然而，在世界各國文化創意產業國際化之浪潮中，台灣之文化創意產業，依然面臨激烈之國際競爭。因此，本文擬以台灣玻璃工藝產業為例，探討該文化創意產業國際化之現況，以供業者或政府發展該項產業之參考。本研究主要是以Welch & Loustarinen(1988) 所提出之六項國際化指標檢驗台灣玻璃工藝國際化之現況。檢驗結果如下:1.玻璃工藝廠商認為在國際化發展時，擁有人力資源、組織結構、財務管理、營運方式、銷售產品、目標市場等能力是重要的，但是企業目前對於這些能力仍然不足，有礙國際化之推動。2.玻璃工藝廠商認為邁向國際化是非常重要的，且對國際化經營的意願頗高， 但政府對於玻璃工藝之輔導政策和人才培育皆嫌不足。3.目前玻璃工藝產業面臨國際化之困境，包括大陸低成本及產品削價競爭，國際行銷能力及經驗不足，未建立自有品牌、人才流失，缺乏研發、創新、創意之能力，營運資金管理不足，政府對於玻璃工藝產業輔導，及資訊管道不足等，有待業者和政府共同努力，逐一剋服。

The world has moved to the age of knowledge economy. The industries of development in each country have expanded to the culture creative industry in response. This industry, therefore, is now sweeping across Europe and America like a tidal wave, and increasingly focused by their developing strategies so as to improving their the international competitiveness .Taiwan is also forced to make the transition from developing the manufacturing industry to the culture creative industry in response to drastic competition from other three Asian Tigers: South Korea, Singapore, Hong Kong, and also from catching-up country like China. The glass craft industry would be selected as the case study in this paper to test its extent of internationalization, and then offer some suggestions to firms and government in developing this industry.The six indicators proposed by Welch & Loustarinen (1988) would be used to test the extent of internationalization of Taiwan’s glass craft industry in this paper. The test results are founded as follows:1. Taiwan’s Glass craft industry lacks of some important factors for internationalization such as well-trained labor forces, organizational structure, financial management, sales promotion, business operation, target market, which would retard the internationalization of this industry.2. The firms of glass craft industry believe that internationalization is very important for them to develop their careers, and they are willing to do so. But government’s policy of developing glass craft industry and the program of training labor forces are not performed well in develop this industry, which would discourage the internationalization of this industry.3. Taiwan’s glass craft industry is falling into the bottleneck of internationalization caused by   the factors such as competition from China with low cost of abundant labor forces, lack of ability and experience in marketing, talents of glass craft industry go away, and the shortages of R&D, innovation, creative, and fund management. These obstacles should be removed away one by one through the cooperation of firms and government in the process of promoting the internationalization of glass craft industry．

